      <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-1" id="add_external_url" data-step-uuid="062D4590-AC77-4D58-A2A6-E4F7AC3184B6">
    <h2 id="add_external_url" class="step-title screensteps-heading">Add External URL</h2>
        <div class="image screensteps-image">
      <img src="https://media.screensteps.com/image_assets/assets/000/773/586/original/9e0f0705-6f44-482b-aba4-316bfcbcde4d.png" srcset="" alt="Add External URL" height="421" width="538">
  </div>
 
      <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock">
  <div id="text-content_81824230-2206-0135-3CE2-22000AB760A3" class="text-block-content">
    <p>In the <strong>Add [Item Type] To:</strong> drop-down menu, select the External URL option.</p>
  </div>
</div>
 
        <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-2" id="" data-step-uuid="04AAE7F3-DA81-404C-864D-EE5FCECF964E">
    
        <div class="image screensteps-image">
      <img src="https://media.screensteps.com/image_assets/assets/000/773/592/original/e3657fed-d122-4391-8bee-1d9e0dbb3086.png" srcset="" alt="Add URL Details" height="421" width="551">
  </div>
 
      <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock">
  <div id="text-content_81827650-2206-0135-3CE4-22000AB760A3" class="text-block-content">
    <p>Type or paste the URL in the URL field [1]. </p>
<p>Give your External URL a page name [2]. </p>
<p>To have the URL open in a new browser tab, click the <strong>Load in a new tab</strong> checkbox [3]. When adding external URLs as module items in the future, the option you select, to open the URL in the existing tab or a new tab, displays as the default.</p>
<p>Choose whether or not to indent the item in the module drop-down menu [4].</p>
  </div>
</div>
 
  </div>
 
  </div>

